Context: DeAille Tam is a graduate of George Brown College's Chef School (2010, 2011, 2012). She was the first female chef in Mainland China to earn a Michelin star in 2018 as the executive chef of Bo Shanghai at Five on the Bund. Tam was named Asia's Best Female Chef, 2021. She and her husband, who is also a George Brown grad, spent a year travelling across China to research cuisine for their restaurant Obscura in Shanghai. Dario Tomaselli taught Tam in the Culinary Management and Culinary Arts — Italian programs at George Brown and recognized her raw talent and intense passion for food. The online ceremony for Asia's 50 Best Restaurants 2021 will celebrate Tam's honour on March 25.
